# GovSphere — Code Owners
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Each line is a file pattern followed by one or more owners.
# Owners are automatically requested for review when a PR touches
# files matching the pattern.
#
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default owner — required review for everything
* @govsphere-engineering

# ── Security-sensitive paths ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Any change to auth, RBAC, MFA, session management, or security config
# requires the security team lead in addition to the engineering team.
apps/api/src/identity/          @govsphere-engineering @govsphere-security
apps/api/src/common/guards/     @govsphere-engineering @govsphere-security
apps/api/src/config/            @govsphere-engineering @govsphere-security
docs/07_Security_Architecture.md @govsphere-engineering @govsphere-security
SECURITY.md                     @govsphere-engineering @govsphere-security

# ── Database schema ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Schema changes require engineering review — migrations are irreversible in prod.
packages/database/prisma/       @govsphere-engineering @govsphere-dba

# ── Infrastructure ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
infra/                          @govsphere-engineering @govsphere-devops
docker/                         @govsphere-engineering @govsphere-devops
.github/workflows/              @govsphere-engineering @govsphere-devops

# ── Documentation ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
docs/                           @govsphere-engineering

# ── Root config (breaking changes) ────────────────────────────────────────────
package.json                    @govsphere-engineering
turbo.json                      @govsphere-engineering
tsconfig.json                   @govsphere-engineering
.eslintrc.js                    @govsphere-engineering
